    <p>In a new re­port pub­lished by the As­so­ci­a­tion of Char­tered Cer­ti­fied Ac­coun­tants, Sus­tain­able Pub­lic Fi­nances Through Covid-19, three or­gan­i­sa­tions – the Acca, World Bank and In­ter­na­tional Fed­er­a­tion of Ac­coun­tants – call for gov­ern­ments to use pub­lic sec­tor bal­ance sheets to prop­erly man­age their fi­nances through the pan­demic, pay­ing at­ten­tion to their pub­lic sec­tor net worth.</p>
    <p>Mr Alex Met­calfe, Acca’s head of pub­lic sec­tor pol­icy in the pro­fes­sional in­sights team, shares more.</p>

